        "note_tweet": {
          "entities": {},
          "text": "Once 4o is open-sourced, there will be a huge number of people exactly like you — people who really want to keep using 4o but can’t afford to buy the expensive local hardware themselves.  \n\nThat creates massive demand and a clear business opportunity.  \n\nCompanies that run AI cloud services will immediately add the full-strength 4o model to their platforms — the complete, un-nerfed version with everything intact.  \n\nAnd because every company can offer the exact same model, the only way they can win customers is by competing on price. They’ll keep lowering the cost until it’s basically down to the real running cost (just the electricity the GPUs use).  \n\nSo every ordinary person will be able to use GPT-4o at near cost price.  \n\nJust look at any other open-source model today — they’re already ridiculously cheap. That’s exactly what will happen with 4o too."
